<i>Give me the same thing
on Samuel Ramos.</i>

947
01:50:37,593 --> 01:50:41,324
Samuel Ramos. That's it?

948
01:50:41,430 --> 01:50:43,159
- That's it.
- Okay.

949
01:51:18,400 --> 01:51:20,300
<i>Gracias.</i>

950
01:51:28,744 --> 01:51:32,373
- Creasy.
- Samuel.

951
01:51:32,481 --> 01:51:34,472
<i>Honey?</i>

952
01:51:38,086 --> 01:51:40,452
What's going on?

953
01:51:42,257 --> 01:51:46,284
That's what I wanna know.
What is going on?

954
01:51:48,730 --> 01:51:51,631
<i>Huh, Sam?</i>

955
01:51:51,733 --> 01:51:53,963
I'm gonna ask your wife a couple
of questions, okay?

956
01:51:54,069 --> 01:51:57,004
You move...

957
01:51:57,105 --> 01:51:59,130
<i>you make one sound...</i>

958
01:51:59,241 --> 01:52:02,335
I'll snatch the life right outta you,
you understand?

959
01:52:09,651 --> 01:52:12,347
What happened, Lisa, hmm?

960
01:52:12,454 --> 01:52:14,354
Were you in on this?

961
01:52:14,456 --> 01:52:18,620
- Or was it just your husband, huh?
- Am I in on what?

962
01:52:18,727 --> 01:52:22,254
You know what I'm talking about... Pita's
kidnapping, her death. Were you a part of it?

963
01:52:22,364 --> 01:52:25,663
- Pita got killed because the ransom got stolen.
- Shut up!

964
01:52:27,202 --> 01:52:29,568
Yeah, the money was stolen.
You're right. He's right.

965
01:52:29,671 --> 01:52:33,198
The money was stolen by Victor Fuentes.
How much was stolen though, huh?

966
01:52:33,308 --> 01:52:36,300
- $2.5 million, right?
- What are you talking about?

967
01:52:36,411 --> 01:52:39,539
He knows what I'm talking about.
$2.5 million. That's what Victor got, isn't it?

968
01:52:39,648 --> 01:52:42,640
- What are you talking about?
- 2.5 million.

969
01:52:42,751 --> 01:52:45,049
<i>2.5 million to your lawyer
Jordan Kalfus...</i>

970
01:52:45,153 --> 01:52:48,281
that he put in an account in the Cayman
Islands, but he won't get a chance to spend it.

971
01:52:51,627 --> 01:52:53,959
What happened to the other five, Sam?

972
01:52:54,062 --> 01:52:56,997
<i>Huh? That's 2.5, 2.5.
What is five from 10?</i>

973
01:52:57,099 --> 01:52:59,624
That's five. What happened
to the other five, Sam? Tell your wife.

974
01:52:59,735 --> 01:53:02,169
<i>- It's your chance to talk.
What happened to the other five?</i>

975
01:53:02,270 --> 01:53:03,635
- You got a wife, Creasy?
- No, I don't have a wife.

976
01:53:03,739 --> 01:53:06,503
Then you'll never know how hard
it could be to tell your wife the truth.

977
01:53:06,608 --> 01:53:08,838
No, you have a wife!
You tell me what happened!

978
01:53:08,944 --> 01:53:11,071
It was in this room
that my father prayed.

979
01:53:11,179 --> 01:53:13,875
- I don't give a fuck about your fucking father!
- My father prayed.

980
01:53:13,982 --> 01:53:17,884
He prayed that his gambling debts and his
infidelities would be forgiven right in this room.

981
01:53:17,986 --> 01:53:20,682
- Samuel! I love you!
- What, Lisa?

982
01:53:20,789 --> 01:53:24,589
- Tell me the truth.
- I didn't inherit a kingdom! That's the truth!

983
01:53:24,693 --> 01:53:27,594
You wanna know the truth?
I inherited his debt and his mess.

984
01:53:27,696 --> 01:53:30,597
- I inherited his lawyer Jordan...
- You tell me what happened to my baby!

985
01:53:30,699 --> 01:53:33,259
Say it! Say it! Say it!

986
01:53:33,368 --> 01:53:35,996
Say it! Say it! Be a fucking man!

987
01:53:39,808 --> 01:53:42,242
Jordan told me she'd sit in a room...

988
01:53:42,344 --> 01:53:44,744
and watch cartoons all day...

989
01:53:44,846 --> 01:53:47,713
and she'd eat ice cream
and we'd have her back in two days.

990
01:53:47,816 --> 01:53:50,410
He lied to me!

991
01:53:50,519 --> 01:53:53,386
That's why he's fucking dead!
I did it!

992
01:53:53,488 --> 01:53:55,547
I did it, Lisa!

993
01:53:55,657 --> 01:53:58,387
I agreed to the kidnapping.

994
01:53:58,493 --> 01:54:01,929
I did it for us...
for the three of us.

995
01:54:10,372 --> 01:54:12,499
I'm so sorry, Lisa.

996
01:54:18,513 --> 01:54:20,481
You kill him.

997
01:54:21,883 --> 01:54:23,783
You kill him or I will.

998
01:54:54,149 --> 01:54:56,117
Huh. You know, they say a, um...

999
01:54:58,520 --> 01:55:01,648
<i>a bullet always tells the truth.</i>

1000
01:55:10,932 --> 01:55:12,900
It never lies.

1001
01:55:25,881 --> 01:55:30,147
It didn't work for me, Samuel, but maybe...

1002
01:55:32,420 --> 01:55:34,980
Maybe it'll work for you.

1003
01:55:44,299 --> 01:55:46,893
<i>I'll pray for you.</i>

1004
01:58:49,351 --> 01:58:51,251
<i>Gracias.</i>

1005
01:59:16,044 --> 01:59:17,944
- Hola?
- Hola.

1006
01:59:18,046 --> 01:59:20,537
<i>- Mr. Creasy?
- Yeah, it's me.</i>

1007
01:59:20,648 --> 01:59:22,709
<i>I traced the PIN for you
and I have an address.</i>

1008
01:59:23,810 --> 01:59:24,810
<i>Yeah?</i>

1009
01:59:24,819 --> 01:59:28,277
<i>The cardholder is Reina Rosas Sanchez,
the wife of The Voice. "</i>

1010
01:59:28,390 --> 01:59:32,656
<i>She lives in Los Arcos,
apartment 26D, Via Appia.</i>

1011
01:59:32,761 --> 01:59:35,229
<i>- Good.
- And another thing.</i>

1012
01:59:35,330 --> 01:59:39,130
<i>Pick up today's paper and you'll have
a picture of The Voice. "</i>

1013
01:59:39,234 --> 01:59:41,202
<i>Good. Thank you.</i>

1014
02:00:44,199 --> 02:00:46,292
Shh, shh, shh.

1015
02:01:49,764 --> 02:01:51,698
<i>Jos? Qu te pasa?</i>

1016
02:03:06,774 --> 02:03:08,605
<i>S.</i>

1017
02:03:08,710 --> 02:03:10,678
Okay.

1018
02:03:18,253 --> 02:03:20,016
Hmm?

1019
02:03:26,527 --> 02:03:27,994
Hmm?

1020
02:03:39,107 --> 02:03:41,007
<i>S.</i>

1021
02:03:41,109 --> 02:03:43,100
Okay. Uh...

1022
02:03:47,448 --> 02:03:49,348
<i>- S?
- S.</i>

1023
02:03:56,557 --> 02:03:59,185
Aurelio Rosas Sanchez. Okay.

1024
02:04:04,065 --> 02:04:05,965
Okay.

1025
02:04:14,409 --> 02:04:16,343
<i>S.</i>

1026
02:04:16,444 --> 02:04:18,844
<i>S.</i>

1027
02:04:18,946 --> 02:04:20,880
Huh?

1028
02:05:17,739 --> 02:05:19,707
<i>Momento.</i>

1029
02:05:49,370 --> 02:05:51,304
<i>Hola, Daniel.</i>

1030
02:05:51,406 --> 02:05:53,271
Seor Creasy.

1031
02:05:53,374 --> 02:05:56,741
Yeah. Yeah, I got your family here.

1032
02:05:56,844 --> 02:05:59,404
<i>Your brother doesn't look too good.</i>

1033
02:05:59,514 --> 02:06:02,779
<i>Yeah, Reina, she's what,
about eight months?</i>

1034
02:06:02,884 --> 02:06:06,945
<i>Huh? You wanna negotiate?</i>

1035
02:06:10,858 --> 02:06:14,521
The most important thing
in life is family.

1036
02:06:14,629 --> 02:06:16,824
<i>Do you agree?</i>

1037
02:06:18,032 --> 02:06:19,932
I agree.

1038
02:06:21,736 --> 02:06:24,204
And there you are.
You have my family.

1039
02:06:24,305 --> 02:06:27,172
Well, most of my family.

1040
02:06:27,275 --> 02:06:31,439
<i>My wife and I are separated.
You know how that is.</i>

1041
02:06:31,546 --> 02:06:35,312
Now, tell me seriously,
h- how much do you want?

1042
02:06:35,416 --> 02:06:37,179
Ah.

1043
02:06:39,720 --> 02:06:42,211
Your brother wants to speak to you.
Yeah, hold on.

1044
02:06:53,301 --> 02:06:56,464
I'm gonna take your family apart
piece by piece. You understand me?

1045
02:06:56,571 --> 02:06:58,630
Piece by piece. Shut up!

1046
02:06:59,841 --> 02:07:02,639
<i>I don't want your money!</i>

1047
02:07:02,743 --> 02:07:06,372
Do you understand me?
You understand me? I want you.

1048
02:07:39,514 --> 02:07:41,607
I'm listening.

1049
02:07:43,050 --> 02:07:46,417
<i>I'm listening, Daniel. I'm listening.</i>

1050
02:07:52,627 --> 02:07:55,926
<i>All right,
I will give you a life for a life.</i>

1051
02:07:57,532 --> 02:08:00,092
Whose life?
What are you talking about?

1052
02:08:00,201 --> 02:08:02,965
<i>Whose life, Daniel? I want you.</i>

1053
02:08:03,070 --> 02:08:06,562
I will give you her life for your life.

1054
02:08:06,674 --> 02:08:11,134
And in exchange,
I will get my life back.

1055
02:08:11,245 --> 02:08:15,238
- What life? Whose life?
- The girl's. Pita's.

1056
02:08:19,153 --> 02:08:23,317
- Pita's dead.
- Creasy!

1057
02:08:23,424 --> 02:08:28,760
<i>I'm a businessman.
A girl dead is worth nothing. She's alive.</i>

1058
02:08:33,067 --> 02:08:35,035
All right.

1059
02:08:36,971 --> 02:08:39,166
I want proof of life. You hear me?

1060
02:08:39,273 --> 02:08:42,242
I want proof of life.
I want... I want...

1061
02:08:42,343 --> 02:08:44,777
I want the name of her bear.
What does she call her bear?

1062
02:08:44,879 --> 02:08:47,507
<i>You tell her to tell you...</i>

1063
02:08:47,615 --> 02:08:51,142
to tell me what she calls her bear.

1064
02:09:19,947 --> 02:09:22,541
- Yeah?
- Creasy.

1065
02:09:22,650 --> 02:09:25,642
<i>She calls the bear Creasy Bear.</i>

1066
02:09:41,569 --> 02:09:43,537
Okay.

1067
02:09:45,373 --> 02:09:47,967
O- Okay.

1068
02:09:48,075 --> 02:09:50,635
I give you your brother,
you give me the girl.

1069
02:09:52,380 --> 02:09:54,712
- All right.
- Where?

1070
02:10:38,392 --> 02:10:40,292
Hello?

1071
02:10:40,394 --> 02:10:43,056
Lisa, listen to me. Don't hang up.

1072
02:10:43,164 --> 02:10:45,359
I think Pita's alive.

1073
02:10:47,168 --> 02:10:49,398
I can't take this anymore.

1074
02:10:49,503 --> 02:10:51,437
Take the road to Puebla.

1075
02:10:51,539 --> 02:10:54,406
Get off junction 34, south side.

1076
02:10:54,508 --> 02:10:56,533
I'll meet you there in two hours.

1077
02:11:41,856 --> 02:11:43,756
So where is she?

1078
02:11:46,293 --> 02:11:49,421
She's right over there.
You see those two cars out there?

1079
02:11:54,735 --> 02:11:58,000
Pita's kidnapper, Daniel...

1080
02:11:58,105 --> 02:12:01,438
this is his brother.

1081
02:12:02,810 --> 02:12:04,937
Here.

1082
02:12:05,045 --> 02:12:08,776
I'm goin' up on the bridge to get Pita.

1083
02:12:08,883 --> 02:12:11,647
<i>If anything goes wrong,
you put it to his head.</i>

1084
02:12:13,220 --> 02:12:15,347
You pull the trigger, all right?

1085
02:12:16,390 --> 02:12:18,915
You understand?

1086
02:12:21,996 --> 02:12:24,362
You don't...

1087
02:12:24,465 --> 02:12:27,730
Let him loose until she's with you.

1088
02:12:27,835 --> 02:12:29,803
You got it?

1089
02:12:32,273 --> 02:12:34,935
And you don't wait for me, okay?

1090
02:12:37,678 --> 02:12:39,407
Yeah.

1091
02:12:39,513 --> 02:12:43,074
- You'll be all right. You okay?
- Yeah.

1092
02:14:28,255 --> 02:14:30,155
Creasy!

1093
02:14:31,926 --> 02:14:33,894
Creasy!

1094
02:14:35,062 --> 02:14:37,530
Creasy!

1095
02:14:53,814 --> 02:14:56,214
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1096
02:14:56,317 --> 02:14:59,013
They didn't hurt you?

1097
02:14:59,119 --> 02:15:01,451
Hi.

1098
02:15:04,191 --> 02:15:08,491
Your mother's waitin' for you. She's right
down there at the end of the bridge.

1099
02:15:08,595 --> 02:15:12,224
- Okay? You go home.
- Okay.

1100
02:15:12,333 --> 02:15:15,063
- All right.
- Where are you goin'?

1101
02:15:18,939 --> 02:15:21,407
I'm goin' home too.

1102
02:15:22,443 --> 02:15:24,343
I'm goin' to Blue Bayou.

1103
02:15:28,615 --> 02:15:31,243
Oh, Hey.

1104
02:15:31,352 --> 02:15:34,685
I got something for you.

1105
02:15:36,757 --> 02:15:38,748
I got the last number too.

1106
02:15:38,859 --> 02:15:41,692
I love you, Creasy.

1107
02:15:44,198 --> 02:15:46,860
And you love me, don't you?

1108
02:15:47,968 --> 02:15:50,061
Yes, I do.

1109
02:15:50,170 --> 02:15:53,367
With all my heart. Pita, go.

1110
02:15:53,474 --> 02:15:55,442
- Go. Run.
- Bye.

1111
02:16:08,989 --> 02:16:10,889
<i>Vamos!</i>

1112
02:16:10,991 --> 02:16:14,256
- Pita! Baby, come here. It's okay.
- Mom!

1113
02:16:14,361 --> 02:16:17,558
<i>- Mom!
- Come on! Okay, I'll let you go now.</i>

1114
02:16:17,664 --> 02:16:19,723
<i>Mom!</i>